\rem Christmas Tract Module.sfm
\ms What does the Bible tell us about Christmas?
\s A Sign from the Lord
\ref ISA 7:14
\pi ($(ISA 7:14))
\rem Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign. Behold, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and shall call his name Immanuel.
\b
\ref MAT 2:10
\pi ($(MAT 2:10))
\rem When they saw the star, they rejoiced exceedingly with great joy.
\b
\ref LUK 2:12
\pi ($(LUK 2:12))
\rem And this will be a sign for you: you will find a baby wrapped in swaddling cloths and lying in a manger.
\s He is Highly Exalted; Prince and King
\ref ISA 9:6
\pi ($(ISA 9:6))
\rem For to us a child is born, to us a son is given; and the government shall be upon his shoulder, and his name shall be called Wonderful Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.
\b
\ref ZEC 9:9
\pi ($(ZEC 9:9))
\rem Rejoice greatly, O daughter of Zion! Shout aloud, O daughter of Jerusalem! Behold, your king is coming to you; righteous and having salvation is he, humble and mounted on a donkey, on a colt, the foal of a donkey.
\b
\ref ACT 5:31
\pi ($(ACT 5:31))
\rem Him hath God exalted with his right hand to be a Prince and a Saviour, for to give repentance to Israel, and forgiveness of sins.
\b
\ref PHP 2:8-10
\pi ($(PHP 2:8-10))
\rem And being found in human form, he humbled himself by becoming obedient to the point of death, even death on a cross. Therefore God has highly exalted him and bestowed on him the name that is above every name, so that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth.
\s The Promised Messiah, Born of a Virgin
\ref ISA 11:1
\pi ($(ISA 11:1))
\rem There shall come forth a shoot from the stump of Jesse, and a branch from his roots shall bear fruit.
\b
\ref MAT 1:21
\pi ($(MAT 1:21))
\rem She will bear a son, and you shall call his name Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.
\b
\ref MAT 1:23
\pi ($(MAT 1:23))
\rem “Behold, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and they shall call his name Immanuel” (which means, God with us).
\b
\ref LUK 1:30-31
\pi ($(LUK 1:30-31))
\rem And the angel said to her, “Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favor with God. And behold, you will conceive in your womb and bear a son, and you shall call his name Jesus.
\b
\ref LUK 2:15-16
\pi ($(LUK 2:15-16))
\rem When the angels went away from them into heaven, the shepherds said to one another, “Let us go over to Bethlehem and see this thing that has happened, which the Lord has made known to us.”And they went with haste and found Mary and Joseph, and the baby lying in a manger.
\s Good News, Great Joy and a Precious Gift
\ref LUK 2:10
\pi ($(LUK 2:10))
\rem And the angel said to them, “Fear not, for behold, I bring you good news of great joy that will be for all the people.
\b
\ref LUK 2:11
\pi ($(LUK 2:11))
\rem For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Savior, who is Christ the Lord.
\b
\ref LUK 2:14
\pi ($(LUK 2:14))
\rem “Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace among those with whom he is pleased!”
\b
\ref JHN 3:16
\pi ($(JHN 3:16))
\rem For God so loved the world, that he gave his only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life.
\b
\ref ROM 6:23
\pi ($(ROM 6:23))
\rem For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.
\b
\ref ROM 15:13
\pi ($(ROM 15:13))
\rem May the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, so that by the power of the Holy Spirit you may abound in hope.
\b
\ref 2CO 9:15
\pi ($(2CO 9:15))
\rem Thanks be unto God for his unspeakable gift.
\b
\ref JAS 1:17
\pi ($(JAS 1:17))
\rem Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights with whom there is no variation or shadow due to change.
